flowRoot.flowPara: Step-by-Step Procedures for Upgrading Your Liferay Portal

Liferay Portal is the leading open source portal in the marketplace today. This is seen through having received awards from multiple leading industry publications, as well as its impressive download rate (over 40,000 downloads a month and over a million downloads total). Why is it so popular? Because Liferay Portal has out of the box all of the features you need to run a successful web site, whether that site is a public Internet site, a corporate Intranet, or anything in between.

The Liferay Portal Administrator's Guide is your complete guide to installing, integrating, configuring, and maintaining Liferay Portal. This comprehensive guide will show you how to install Liferay Portal, configure it for your use, and maintain your Liferay-powered site on a day-to-day basis. From installing a bundle to configuring a Liferay cluster, every aspect of running Liferay Portal is covered.

This newly-updated guide is your roadmap to a successful implementation of Liferay Portal. Now covering Liferay Portal 5.1 and below, this book contains the information you need to keep your portal environment running smoothly.

About the Author: Richard L. Sezov, Jr. is Liferay's Knowledge Manager. He has been building portals for Fortune 500 companies and non-profits since 2003, and has written material for several of Liferay's training courses.
